l only keep going down.  Anyone else notice we see about 1 person a day posting that they are leaving?  Well it's just going to get worst.  My original guild all quit and the one I'm in now has had about 25 quit as well because they couldn't take it.<br>
<br>
Anyone agree with me that some changes are needed?  Or do you like playing on a server where around 50% of the zones are totally empty and another 25% have 1 group in them.  I don't know, but finding someone who can find a group daily is getting pretty damned hard.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxharian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xharian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 5:20:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is dying... slowly but surely</span><hr size=1> I have played UO, AC and DAoC before coming over to Norrath -- FirionaVie is my first EQ server. Just wanted to note that FV's been the only gaming environment where I got invited to groups after a simple /wave...before i could say a &quot;Hail friend(s)&quot; A great majority seems to only /con you, not even asking your class or level. I must confess I have recently taken a look at several other servers, but don't think I can play on a regular server...I love this server, met wonderful people during my travels---just wish there were twice as many players as the current number. <br>
<br>
Anrathal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=celle>Celle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 5:37:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is dying... slowly but surely</span><hr size=1> Eek, this is not the kind of post I am happy seeing as a new player. It does seem like a lot of people have been quitting, but I am not sure the ruleset is entirely to blame. From what I have noticed it is usually those who have played the game for years, and are just totally burnt out.<br>
<br>
I think we a need a little more optimism here. Remember, there aren't a lot of players, but we CAN do something about it. Feneant may be right that some adjustment of the ruleset is necessary. Making it a BIT easier to learn languages would be a good start. <br>
<br>
The strategy I use is to help those who are new to the server and/or the game have as much fun as possible. Word of mouth can be a huge help when there are 30 servers to choose from and FV is at the bottom (well, top technically)<br>
<br>
Also, MANY players do not have any roleplaying backgrounds whatsoever. Those of us who do need to show them what it's al about, and how much it adds to the fun. I admit it may not be for everyone, but for me at least it gives depth to the game that isn't found in camping the mobs that give you the best XP.<br>
<br>
I think those players that quit FV after a short while didn't have that one really fun experience that you can only get on OUR server. As I've heard over and over on these boards, there is no going back! That said, we DO need more players to keep to fun going, so lets discuss and come up with ideas... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uebine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ebine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 5:42:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is dying... slowly but surely</span><hr size=1> Hmm I see a lot of new people running around. I know that the other servers see people come and go to. First off I have to say that you will see odd groups on this server. Most normal servers will only have 5 in a group but not give you a spot because they are waiting for that perfect fit they want. On this server its oh we have an enchanter but what the heck we can have two.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 217<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 6:23:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The new folk ..</span><hr size=1> .. don't usually make it past level 5.  The tougher ones stick around to 15 or even 20, but it gets really empty around 25'ish.  I can run through zones that are great hunting grounds at that level and find no one at all.  There's only one person still on my friends list that I added before level 10.<br>
<br>
It seems like there's maybe one hot-spot for grouping for each of the major level ranges.  I've noticed that iceclad seems to be good for the 35'ish folk.  By good, I mean there's more than 2 people in the zone and they seem to be doing pickup groups (I was just there to get a mask).<br>
<br>
I'm not sure what's causing it, but I suspect it's one of three: language, TLC, or character limit.  All of them can result in severe frustration if you don't carefully plan out your entire character from 1 to 60 and know precisely which class you want to play all the way up.  The FV ruleset is not for folks that don't plan ahead or don't know how to plan ahead because they're new.<br>
<br>
Shintou keeps railing about how the PG'ers are destroying his RP.  Well, the ruleset here is such that only a PG'er can survive.  IMHO, if FV was turned into a normal blue server, we wouldn't see a huge inrush of &quot;farming d00ds&quot;.  We'd just keep the ones that chose FV for the &quot;roleplay prefered&quot; description on the server lists. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/19/02 6:27:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 8:12:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The new folk ..</span><hr size=1> do Verant employees even bother to read the polls, input and feedback from forums such as these? <br>
<br>
I'm not trying to flame, I'm just being pragmatic. I'm just wondering if anything will ever come out of these threads. <br>
<br>
1) you have grievances with some parts of the server ruleset <br>
2) only Verant developers can make those changes<br>
3) are Verant developers hearing any of this? <br>
<br>
