<font color=purple>
<br>
<b>Sakurajosui Ko`Rn (High Elf Cleric) [Merciless]
<br></b></font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujaroo1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaroo1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 9:12:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh..</span><hr size=1> This is my first server and only server that I have played on in EQ.  I started back in october.<br>
Since that time I have joined a really good guild (tinkers pride) and I learned through that about people leaving.  Once we had, I believe, over 30 members and now we have about 15 regulars.  I don't thank that is bad at all for a guild made up of only gnomes, but still...  For awhile I feared it was going to dip below 10 AND we are on our second guild leader.  If I'm not the longest running member then I don't know who else in the guild is!<br>
So, yeah, I know what your talking about.  The busiest city I have seen is Kelethin, but it's still not as busy as it used to be.<br>
Anyway, I have experiance with roleplaying which is why I chose this server and now with my new background, well, I can't wait to get into it more even if the populations not that high.  I will be loyal to my guild and this server until the end.  Which, either way, I hope never comes.<br>
<br>
Jaroo Dooger<br>
Officer of Tinkers Pride<br>
Wizard of 23 seasons <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxarshulshadowheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xarshul Shadowheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 10:04:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh..</span><hr size=1> Killer pics btw MelMell :+) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 10:07:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh..</span><hr size=1> I think that if they made this server a normal blue, we'd get alot more people and keep them, but I'm not sure if they'd be exactly what we wanted.  If you want a normal blue server with a low pop but big enough to find groups, try Lanys T'vyl.  It was never TOO big for me, or too little either.<br>
<br>
FV is the last refuge of alot of people.  When they get their parade rained on here, they just leave.  I'd leave if not for FV, and if our server changed and DID get overrun by farmers, I'd be gone faster than you could blink.  There are other games out there where I won't have to put up with the legions, but none of those have the atmosphere FV does. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 10:25:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is dying... slowly but surely</span><hr size=1> When do you play? Are you good or evil (or neutral)? Are you in a guild or have you made many friends?<br>
<br>
I've had less problems finding groups on FV than I have on E'ci. In fact the lower population has made it EASIER to find groups. &quot;Balanced&quot; groups are another matter.<br>
<br>
I think the lower population helps a lot. Very rarely will you be turned down for a group because you aren't the class/role the group needs. Instead they'll take you and adapt.<br>
<br>
I've got a growing list a friends that I check for and see who's got room. Luclin has made travel much easier, and I spend a lot of time in a lot of different zones, not just hotspots.<br>
<br>
BTW if you're thinking of starting/re-starting in FV, consider a warrior/paladin/shadowknight. They seem to be few in number. But that's just what I'm seeing.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 259<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/19/02 10:30:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: heh..</span><hr size=1> 1) you have grievances with some parts of the server ruleset <br>
<br>
Only anon<br>
<br>
2) only Verant developers can make those changes<br>
<br>
Sad but True<br>
<br>
3) are Verant developers hearing any of this? <br>
<br>
Would they care if they did?<br>
<br>
I was among the first to start, I was the 4th player in Qeynos North, I'm 42 and still going, but man, there has to be something done to change it.  I play EQ on FV only and the second FV goes, my account gets cancelled again.  I watched my brother play on another server and it sickened me, it was like IRC or ICQ with graphics and more to do, but for every new player we get, 3 leave.  Quite frequently, we stand below the diety PvP server now... I'm not writing this thread as a whine, I'm writing it to say that we have to do something before Verant decides that the server isn't lucrative and offer to either send us to another server or remove the rules on ours to make it a blue server with RP preferred.<br>
<br>
<br>
I was considering asking Verant for 1 thing and 1 thing only, to remove anon to at least help us in getting groups... we went through most of the LFG today to find someone to join us and the closest we found was 5 lower than the lowest member in our group.  The other day when I asked those LFG, I got one that was 13 over our highest and one 15 under our lowest...  It's not a drastic change, but it does at least alleviate the whole grouping problems. <br>
<br>
